.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-env-get - Get details of an environment


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock env get  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show full details of one environment - connection endpoints (web client,
SOAP, OData v4, dev endpoint, downloads), BC admin credentials, status,
and timestamps.

.PP
Output formats:
  -o table  (default) vertical key/value layout, one field per line
  -o json   the full env record from the API (use for scripting)
  -o csv    the same compact row as 'env list' (one entry)

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  4   rate-limited
  5   environment not found


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for get


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock env get my-env
  bcdock env get my-env -o json
  bcdock env get a1b2c3d4
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-env(1)\fP
